SIMPLE: thicken
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thicken
<hw>Thick"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Thickened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Thickening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make thick (in any
sense of the word).</def> <specif>Specifically:</specif> --⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(a)</sd> <def>To render dense; to inspissate; <as>as, to
<ex>thicken</ex> paint</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>To make close; to fill up interstices in; <as>as,
to <ex>thicken</ex> cloth; to <ex>thicken</ex> ranks of trees or
men</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <def>To strengthen; to confirm.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And this may to <qex>thicken</qex> other proofs.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(d)</sd> <def>To make more frequent; <as>as, to <ex>thicken</ex>
blows</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thicken</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thicken
<hw>Thick"en</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become thick.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Thy luster <xex>thickens</xex> when he shines by.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The press of people <qex>thickens</qex> to the court.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The combat <qex>thickens</qex>, like the storm that flies.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thickening</ent>⟦br⟧
